# Backend Environment Variables Configuration

This guide explains all environment variables needed for the Hidden Gem backend.

## Setup Instructions

1. Copy `.env.example` to `.env`:
   ```bash
   cp .env.example .env
   ```

2. Update values with your actual configuration

3. Never commit `.env` to Git (already in `.gitignore`)

## Environment Variables

### Application Settings

```env
# Application Environment
NODE_ENV=development
# Options: development, staging, production

# Server Configuration
PORT=3000
# The port where backend server runs

APP_NAME=Hidden Gem API
APP_VERSION=1.0.0
LOG_LEVEL=debug
# Options: debug, info, warn, error
```

### Database

```env
# PostgreSQL Database
DATABASE_HOST=localhost
DATABASE_PORT=5432
DATABASE_NAME=hidden_gem
DATABASE_USER=postgres
DATABASE_PASSWORD=your_strong_password
DATABASE_SSL=false
# Set to true in production

# For production, use managed database:
# DATABASE_HOST=db.production.aws.com
# DATABASE_SSL=true
```

### Redis

```env
# Redis Cache & Queue
REDIS_HOST=localhost
REDIS_PORT=6379
REDIS_PASSWORD=
# Leave empty if no auth
REDIS_DB=0
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0
# Complete URL (alternative to separate configs)
```

### JWT Authentication

```env
# JWT Secrets (generate with: openssl rand -base64 32)
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key_here
JWT_EXPIRE=15m
# Token expiration time (15 minutes recommended)

JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=your_super_secret_refresh_key_here
JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRE=7d
# Refresh token expiration (7 days recommended)
```

### OAuth2 Configuration

```env
# Google OAuth
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=xxx.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/auth/google/callback

# Apple OAuth
APPLE_CLIENT_ID=com.hidden-gem.app
APPLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_apple_client_secret
APPLE_TEAM_ID=XXXXX
APPLE_KEY_ID=XXXXX
# For production:
# APPLE_KEY_ID=your_apple_key_id
# APPLE_REDIRECT_URI=https://api.hidden-gem.app/auth/apple/callback
```

### Firebase Cloud Messaging

```env
# Firebase Service Account (for push notifications)
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_PATH=./firebase-service-account.json
# Download from Firebase Console → Project Settings → Service Accounts

FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-firebase-project-id
FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_firebase_api_key
```

### Elasticsearch

```env
# Elasticsearch for full-text search
ELASTICSEARCH_URL=http://localhost:9200
# For production, use managed Elasticsearch (e.g., AWS OpenSearch)
# ELASTICSEARCH_URL=https://your-domain.es.us-east-1.amazonaws.com:443

ELASTICSEARCH_INDEX_PREFIX=hidden_gem
# Prefix for all indices (e.g., hidden_gem_places, hidden_gem_users)

ELASTICSEARCH_ENABLED=true
# Set to false to disable ES (will use database search fallback)
```

### AWS S3 Media Storage

```env
# AWS S3 for image storage
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_aws_access_key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_aws_secret_key
AWS_S3_BUCKET=hidden-gem-media
# Bucket name on S3

# CloudFront CDN (optional, for faster image delivery)
AWS_CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN=d123456.cloudfront.net
# If set, images served through CloudFront URL instead of S3

# S3 Configuration
AWS_S3_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_S3_ACL=public-read
# ACL for uploaded objects (private recommended for user data)
```

### Email Service

```env
# Email Configuration (for transactional emails)
MAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com
MAIL_PASSWORD=your_app_specific_password
MAIL_FROM=noreply@hidden-gem.app

# Or use SendGrid
SENDGRID_API_KEY=your_sendgrid_api_key
SENDGRID_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@hidden-gem.app
SENDGRID_ENABLED=false
# Set to true to use SendGrid instead of SMTP

# Or use other services (Mailgun, AWS SES, etc.)
```

### Third-party Services

```env
# Sentry (Error Tracking)
SENTRY_DSN=https://key@sentry.io/123456
SENTRY_ENABLED=false
# Set to true in production for error monitoring

# Stripe (Payments, if applicable)
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxxxx
STRIPE_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_test_xxxxx
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxxxx

# Twilio (SMS notifications, if applicable)
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=your_twilio_sid
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=your_twilio_token
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=+1234567890
```

### CORS & Security

```env
# CORS Configuration
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:8081
# Comma-separated list of allowed origins
# In production: https://app.hidden-gem.app

# CSRF Protection
CSRF_ENABLED=true
SESSION_SECRET=your_session_secret_key
```

### File Upload

```env
# File Upload Configuration
MAX_FILE_SIZE=10485760
# Maximum file size in bytes (10MB default)

UPLOAD_DIR=./uploads
# Local directory for uploads (if S3 unavailable)

ALLOWED_IMAGE_FORMATS=jpeg,png,webp,gif
ALLOWED_IMAGE_TYPES=image/jpeg,image/png,image/webp,image/gif
```

### Pagination

```env
# Default Pagination
DEFAULT_PAGE_LIMIT=20
# Items per page (default)

MAX_PAGE_LIMIT=100
# Maximum items per page (prevent abuse)
```

### Feature Flags

```env
# Feature toggles (enable/disable features without redeploying)
FEATURE_OAUTH_ENABLED=true
FEATURE_SEARCH_ENABLED=true
FEATURE_NOTIFICATIONS_ENABLED=true
FEATURE_IMAGE_OPTIMIZATION=true
FEATURE_ELASTICSEARCH=true
FEATURE_BULLMQ_ENABLED=true
```

### Monitoring & Logging

```env
# Logging Service
LOG_LEVEL=info
LOG_FORMAT=json
# Options: json, simple

# APM (Application Performance Monitoring)
APM_ENABLED=false
APM_SERVER_URL=http://localhost:8200
# For Elastic APM integration

# Health Check
HEALTH_CHECK_ENABLED=true
HEALTH_CHECK_PATH=/health
```

